---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy | JuryPress">
  <div class="box">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>JuryPress operates as a static site and does not collect personal data on its servers. There is no account registration, and we never ask for your name, address, or payment details.</p>
    <p>We use the following third-party services, which set cookies and collect usage data under their own privacy policies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics 4 (Firebase Analytics)</strong> — records which pages are viewed, time on page, referral source, approximate region, and browser/device type. This data does not identify you personally.</li>
      <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — serves third-party ads on review pages and may use cookies to personalise them.</li>
      <li><strong>giscus (GitHub Discussions)</strong> — powers the comment section on review pages. Posting a comment requires a GitHub account, in which case GitHub's privacy policy applies.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can opt out of analytics with the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>, and adjust ad personalisation in your <a href="https://myadcenter.google.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads settings</a>.</p>
    <p>JuryPress is published by PixApps. See the <a href="https://pixapps.ai/privacy">PixApps privacy policy</a> for the policy covering pixapps.ai as a whole.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
<style>
  .box {
    background: #fafafa;
    border: 1px solid #eee;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
</style>
